<main id="content" class="content"> <header> <h1 class="title">A Prayer for Wellness</h1>
 <p class="subtitle" role="doc-subtitle">Jan 13, 2015 00:00</p>
</header> <p>
Jesus saw the lame man at the pool, <br></br>
and asked, “Do you want to be made well?” <br></br>
Instead of an answer, <br></br>
the man gave an explanation. <br></br></p>

 <p>
But explanations become rationalizations, <br></br>
and rationalizations become excuses, <br></br>
and “Yes, but…” just means “No, thank you.” <br></br></p>

 <p>
Lord, <br></br></p>

 <p>
Forgive us for preferring <br></br>
the familiarity of the present pain <br></br>
to the joy of new life that you offer. <br></br></p>

 <p>
 <i>Amen</i>
</p>



